Package com.credenceid.database

Interface BiometricDatabase

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BiometricsManager
    public interface BiometricDatabase
    Use to perform Biometrics Enrolment, Matching, Verify other operations using Fingerprints and Face biometric templates. The Threshold to use depends on provider specific activated :

    Neurotechnology (C-SDK internal Threshold = 85)
    FAR (false acceptance rate) Matching threshold (score)
    100 % 0
    10 % 12
    1 % 24
    0.1 % 36
    0.01 % 48
    0.001 % 60
    0.0001 % 72
    0.0001 % 84
    0.00001 % 96

    Innovatrics (C-SDK internal Threshold = 40)
    FAR (false acceptance rate) Matching threshold (score)
    1 % 20
    0.1 % 30
    0.01 % 40
    0.001 % 50

    Huawei (C-SDK internal Threshold = 15) (Can be used with CredenceID database provider)
    FAR (false acceptance rate) Matching threshold (score)
    1 % 68
    0.1 % 73

    • Method Detail

      • enroll

        void enroll​(int ID,
            FingerprintRecord finger,
            FaceRecord face,
            IrisRecord iris,
            BiometricDatabase.OnEnrollCallback callback)
        Asynchronously enrolls data to database. Allows data to be enrolled for either a new user or an existing record.

        If you would like to have database automatically assign an ID then pass -1 for the ID.

        Possible Error Returns Codes
        • BiometricDatabase.Status.ERR_RECORD_NOT_FOUND: If a record ID is given, but no associated record is found.
        • BiometricDatabase.Status.ERR_BAD_FINGERPRINT_DATA: If any fingerprint object inside fingerprintData parameter is invalid, meaning invalid fingerprint image or a fingerprint template cannot be made.
        • BiometricDatabase.Status.ERR_BAD_FACE_DATA: If faceData parameter is invalid, meaning invalid face image or a face template cannot be made.
        • BiometricDatabase.Status.ERR_BAD_IRIS_DATA: If any iris object inside irisData parameter is invalid, meaning iris image or an iris template cannot be made.
        • BiometricDatabase.Status.SUCCESS: If enrollment was successful.
        Parameters:
        finger - Fingerprint data to enroll.
        face - Face data to enroll.
        iris - Iris data to enroll.
        callback - Method invoked when operation returns back with some result.

      • verify

        void verify​(int ID,
            FingerprintRecord finger,
            FaceRecord face,
            IrisRecord iris,
            BiometricDatabase.OnVerifyCallback callback)
        Asynchronously matches given biometric data against a record ID in database.

        Possible Error Returns Codes
        • BiometricDatabase.Status.ERR_RECORD_NOT_FOUND: If a record ID is given, but no associated record is found.
        • BiometricDatabase.Status.ERR_BAD_FINGERPRINT_DATA: If any fingerprint object inside fingerprintData parameter is invalid, meaning invalid fingerprint image or a fingerprint template cannot be made.
        • BiometricDatabase.Status.ERR_BAD_FACE_DATA: If faceData parameter is invalid, meaning invalid face image or a face template cannot be made.
        • BiometricDatabase.Status.ERR_BAD_IRIS_DATA: If any iris object inside irisData parameter is invalid, meaning iris image or an iris template cannot be made.
        • BiometricDatabase.Status.SUCCESS: If match took place and returned with a result.
        Parameters:
        ID - Record ID to match against.
        finger - Fingerprint data to verify against.
        face - Face data to verify against.
        iris - Iris data to verify against.
        callback - Method invoked when operation returns back with some result.

      • verify

        void verify​(int ID,
            FingerprintRecord[] fingers,
            FaceRecord face,
            IrisRecord[] irises,
            BiometricDatabase.OnVerifyCallback callback)

        • BiometricDatabase.Status.ERR_BAD_FINGERPRINT_DATA: If any fingerprint object inside fingerprintData parameter is invalid, meaning invalid fingerprint image or a fingerprint template cannot be made.
        • BiometricDatabase.Status.ERR_BAD_FACE_DATA: If faceData parameter is invalid, meaning invalid face image or a face template cannot be made.
        • BiometricDatabase.Status.ERR_BAD_IRIS_DATA: If any iris object inside irisData parameter is invalid, meaning iris image or an iris template cannot be made.
        • BiometricDatabase.Status.SUCCESS: If match took place and returned with a result.
        Parameters:

        fingers - Fingerprint data to verify against.

        • BiometricDatabase.Status.ERR_BAD_IRIS_DATA: If any iris object inside irisData parameter is invalid, meaning iris image or an iris template cannot be made.
        • BiometricDatabase.Status.SUCCESS:: If match took place and returned with results.
        Parameters:

        face - Face data to match against.
        iris - Iris data to match against.
        callback - Method invoked when operation returns back with some result.
